# GEX Maximum Fragility Indicator

A tiered signal system (Levels 1–3) measuring short-term market fragility 
driven by low Gamma Exposure (GEX) combined with negative price momentum.

## What it does
Detects rapid, sharp market shocks (–2% to –5% over 1–2 days) that occur 
when low dealer gamma exposure removes the market's structural volatility 
buffer — distinct from slow, grinding sell-offs where GEX remains stable. 
Signal conviction (Level 1–3) is based on the alignment of GEX percentile, 
GEX velocity/acceleration, and price weakness, and is designed to size 
positions and holding periods for options hedging strategies accordingly.

## Method
Rolling percentile ranking of GEX (252-day lookback), first- and 
second-derivative velocity/acceleration tracking (MACD-style), and 
confirmation logic that separates genuine dealer-hedging shocks from 
ordinary volatility.
